The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, which was based on the recommendations of the campaign commanders, was the only one possible and likely to be so successful that the newspapers at present do not speak at all of Iraq.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, but, objectively speaking, he left his successor with a much more favourable final situation than one could expect.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan the miracle will happen again
It was again the campaign commanders who asked him for an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the White House's reluctance in spite of the habits of subordination.
