How much should you be paid according to your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can know the salary they would deserve according to their profile, thanks to a new application of Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of classified real estate ads, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The tool "How much should you be paid?" calculates user salaries from more than 140,000 job offers available to Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you must register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
For a week now the application has been running, the search engine has detected that, as a general rule, the Spanish worker "feels poorly paid", explained in a statement the product manager of Trovit, Albert Ribera.
According to data available to Trovit from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are the least well paid.
A British computer programmer receives 45 226 gross euros per year and a Frenchman receives 31 059 euros, while a Spanishman receives 24 000 euros.
Similarly, a driver receives EUR 34 247 per annum in England, EUR 25 751 per annum in France and EUR 16 420 per annum in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is that of waiter, with 11 592 euros net annually, followed by that of seller, with 14 725 euros, and that of worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most sought-after jobs on the Internet in the last three months are that of driver, part-time and social workers.
